d-49b1-bad3-c1c3554690aa%5C%22%3EPatriot%20missiles%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225568%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20MIM-104%20Patriot%20Surface-to-Air%20Missile%20System%20assigned%20to%20the%2011th%20Air%20Defense%20Artillery%20Brigade%20fires%20during%20a%20joint%20live-fire%20exercise%20with%20military%20members%20from%20the%20Royal%20Netherlands%20Ground-based%20Air%20Defense%20Command%20at%20McGregor%20Range%2C%20N.M.%2C%20May%2011%2C%202024.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a9989cfd4fbd083f29915e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223712%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20MIM-104%20Patriot%20system%20has%20been%20a%20key%20air%20defense%20system%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%3Cp%3EUS%20Army%20photo%20by%20Sgt.%20David%20Rincon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20US%20weapon%20seeing%20notably%20increased%20production%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-israel-fight-iran-air-defenses-vital-in-modern-war-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPatriot%20Advanced%20Capability-3%20(PAC-3)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20interceptors%20fired%20by%20the%20MIM-104%20Patriot%20mobile%20surface-to-air%20missile%20defense%20system.%20In%20January%2C%20Lockheed%20Martin%20and%20the%20Pentagon%20reached%20a%20seven-year%20deal%20to%20boost%20PAC-3%20amounts%20from%20600%20a%20year%20to%202%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20demand%20for%20these%20weapons%20has%20been%20demonstrated%20by%20US%20forces%2C%20as%20well%20as%20American%20allies%20and%20partners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fproduction-of-patriot-missiles-surging-demand-exceptionally-high-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPatriot%20air%20defense%20batteries%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20comprise%20radar%20and%20control%20systems%2C%20launcher%20stations%2C%20and%20interceptor%20missiles%2C%20are%20among%20the%20world's%20best%20air%20defense%20systems%2C%20detecting%20and%20intercepting%20ballistic%20missiles%2C%20cruise%20missiles%2C%20drones%2C%20and%20aircraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPatriots%20have%20seen%20combat%20since%20the%20Gulf%20War%2C%20and%20in%20recent%20years%20have%20been%20a%20core%20defensive%20element%20against%20Iranian%20missile%20and%20drone%20attacks%20against%20Israel%20and%20across%20the%20Middle%20East.%2019%20countries%20operate%20Patriots%20around%20the%20world%2C%20including%20European%20and%20Middle%20Eastern%20allies%2C%20demonstrating%20global%20demand%20for%20batteries%20and%20missiles%2C%20which%20take%20years%20to%20produce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20other%20weaponry%20in%20the%20US%20stockpile%2C%20Washington%20has%20transferred%20Patriots%20to%20Ukraine%20throughout%20its%20war%20against%20Russia.%20Ukraine%20has%20used%20its%20Patriots%20to%20intercept%20Russian%20missile%20and%20drone%20barrages%2C%20and%20its%20reliance%20on%20the%20weapon%20has%20strained%20stockpiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20paused%20weapons%20shipments%2C%20including%20more%20Patriot%20interceptors%2C%20to%20Ukraine%20last%20year%20amid%20concerns%20about%20US%20stockpiles.%20US%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20later%20reversed%20the%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22406d7f5c-2f14-46fd-8f09-997ddc34a0ad%5C%22%3EPrSM%20weapons%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222878%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20US%20military%20video%20shows%20a%20PrSM%20missile%20launch.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a8525fd3e2f1aef369f6cc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221580%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Precision%20Strike%20Missile%20(PrSM)%20launch.%3Cp%3EUS%20Central%20Command%2FScreengrab%20via%20X%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%20announced%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20the%20Pentagon%20and%20Lockheed%20Martin%20are%20in%20the%20process%20of%20accelerating%20production%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Firan-war-proving-ground-for-newest-us-weapons-missile-drone-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPrecision%20Strike%20Missile%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%20goal%20of%20quadrupling%20the%20number%20of%20missiles%20made%20to%20400%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrSM%20is%20a%20new%20short-range%20surface-to-surface%20missile%20that%20made%20its%20combat%20debut%20this%20month%20against%20Iran%2C%20which%20Adm.%20Brad%20Cooper%2C%20the%20head%20of%20US%20Central%20Command%2C%20said%20was%20%26quot%3Ba%20historic%20first%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Ban%20unrivaled%2C%20deep-strike%20capability.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrSM%20can%20be%20fired%20from%20an%20M142%20High%20Mobility%20Artillery%20Rocket%20System%2C%20or%20HIMARS%2C%20launcher%20and%20is%20estimated%20to%20cost%20%241.6%20million%20on%20the%20low%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ffd8fbc2-9d09-4988-bb25-2417329441f8%5C%22%3EDeeper%20arsenals%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Standard%20Missile%20-3%20Block%20IIA%2C%20or%20SM-3%20Blk%20IIA%2C%20is%20launched%20from%20US%20Navy%20Arleigh%20Burke-class%20guided%20missile%20destroyer%20USS%20McCampbell%20(DDG%2085)%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20the%20Pacific%20Missile%20Range%20Facility%2C%20Hawaii%2C%20during%20Flight%20Test%20Other-23%20or%20FTX-23%2C%20February%208%2C%202024.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b427aea7a4f9df67ba4b7a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20US%20Navy%20has%20used%20SM-3s%20on%20three%20occasions%20to%20defend%20Turkish%20airspace%20over%20the%20past%20two%20weeks.%3Cp%3EUS%20Missile%20Defense%20Agency%20photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20officials%20have%20said%20that%20increased%20production%20of%20critical%20missiles%20and%20interceptors%20isn't%20aimed%20solely%20at%20replenishing%20stockpiles%20but%20is%20instead%20about%20expanding%20them%20so%20that%20American%20forces%20have%20a%20greater%20number%20of%20munitions%20for%20high-end%20fights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20key%20benchmark%20for%20such%20munitions%20requirements%20has%20been%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20fight%20with%20China%2C%20which%20would%20require%20deep%20stockpiles%20of%20missiles%20able%20to%20engage%20land%2C%20maritime%2C%20and%20air%20targets%2C%20as%20well%20as%20robust%20air%20defenses%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-military-china-missile-problem-getting-worse-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EChina's%20missile%20threat%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-ramping-up-production-of-weapons-critical-for-major-war-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1774516021000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c4179348461c18d7be5f88%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-ramping-up-production-of-weapons-critical-for-major-war-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22From%20Tomahawk%20missiles%20to%20THAAD%20interceptor%20seekers%2C%20the%20US%20is%20massively%20increasing%20its%20production%20rates%20for%20key%20munitions%20amid%20stockpile%20concerns.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cpanella%40businessinsider.com%20(Chris%20Panella)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-ramping-up-production-of-weapons-critical-for-major-war-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20burned%20out%20as%20a%20manager%20at%20Microsoft%20%E2%80%94%20then%20got%20laid%20off.%20Nearly%203%20years%20later%2C%20I'm%20still%20looking%20for%20work.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221119%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Karena%20Plepel%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c2e59658b5806618e7df0b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22839%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKarena%20Plepel%3Cp%3EKarena%20Plepel%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EKarena%20Plepel%20was%20laid%20off%20from%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-manager-laid-off-great-flattening-next-career-move-2025-7%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emanager%20role%20at%20Microsoft%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20July%202023.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENearly%20three%20years%20later%2C%20she%20still%20hasn't%20found%20work%2C%20which%20has%20been%20difficult%20both%20financially%20and%20mentally.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDespite%20her%20challenges%2C%20she%20believes%20everything%20happens%20for%20a%20reason.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Karena%20Plepel%2C%20a%2043-year-old%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3Ejob%20seeker%20who%20lives%20in%20Illinois.%20She%20previously%20worked%20for%20Microsoft%20as%20a%20senior%20hub%20manager%20until%20being%20laid%20off%20in%202023.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20last%20few%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-ceo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eyears%20at%20Microsoft%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20a%20roller%20coaster%20%E2%80%94%20one%20that%20ended%20with%20me%20losing%20my%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20July%2010%2C%202023%2C%20I%20was%20pulled%20into%20an%20unexpected%20meeting%20with%20some%20of%20my%20colleagues%3B%20we%20had%20a%20sinking%20feeling%20about%20what%20it%20meant.%20Then%2C%20we%20learned%20we'd%20been%20laid%20off.%20The%20news%20didn't%20come%20as%20a%20complete%20surprise%2C%20but%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20it%20was%20surprising%20since%20I'd%20survived%20so%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-layoffs-more-than-1000-jobs-sales-customer-service-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eprior%20layoff%20cycles%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%2C%20it%20will%20be%20three%20years%20since%20I%20was%20laid%20off%2C%20and%20I'm%20still%20looking%20for%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ec436bed-76bf-4c4a-8236-80ea24e7f519%5C%22%3EI%20worked%20in%20many%20different%20roles%20within%20Microsoft%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20working%20for%20Microsoft%20in%202010%20as%20a%20sales%20representative%2C%20later%20becoming%20a%20store%20manager%20at%20a%20retail%20location%20in%20Schaumburg%2C%20Illinois.%20When%20the%20pandemic%20hit%20in%202020%2C%20Microsoft%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-will-shut-down-retail-stores-2020-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclosed%20its%20retail%20locations%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20my%20responsibilities%20and%20titles%20rapidly%20evolved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20next%20few%20years%2C%20I%20went%20from%20being%20a%20physical%20store%20manager%20to%20a%20remote%20store%20manager%20to%20a%20territory%20sales%20manager%2C%20and%20finally%20to%20senior%20hub%20manager%2C%20which%20I%20began%20in%20August%202022.%20In%20that%20position%2C%20I%20was%20a%20manager%20of%20managers%2C%20with%20five%20direct%20reports%20overseeing%20more%20than%2050%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20my%20role%20changes%2C%20this%20period%20also%20felt%20like%20a%20roller%20coaster%20because%20of%20the%20turnover%20at%20the%20company.%20Some%20people%20left%20as%20part%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-chris-capossela-retail-store-closures-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshift%20away%20from%20retail%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20many%20people%20in%20the%20Xbox%20division%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-layoffs-widespread-xbox-azure-government-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elost%20their%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Overall%2C%20it%20was%20a%20high-anxiety%20time.%20You%20never%20knew%20if%20you%20would%20be%20next.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20waves%20of%20layoffs%2C%20mine%20came.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20thing%20I%20thought%20about%20was%20my%20team%20members%20who%20had%20also%20been%20affected%2C%20and%20I%20went%20into%20%26quot%3Bleader%20crisis%20mode.%26quot%3B%20I%20set%20up%20a%20meeting%20with%20my%20team%20so%20we%20could%20process%20what%20had%20happened%20and%20talk%20through%20their%20questions.%20I%20also%20followed%20up%20with%20HR%20and%20helped%20organize%20a%20broader%20call%2C%20so%20people%20across%20teams%20could%20get%20their%20questions%20answered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20layoff%20meeting%20had%20felt%20so%20sterile%2C%20and%20I%20wanted%20to%20help%20make%20the%20process%20feel%20more%20personal%20and%20human%20for%20those%20who%20were%20impacted.%20Microsoft%20had%20been%20such%20a%20caring%20company%20up%20to%20that%20point%2C%20and%20I%20just%20couldn't%20have%20that%20be%20the%20ending%20for%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20is%20speaking%20with%20workers%20who've%20found%20themselves%20at%20a%20corporate%20crossroads%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20due%20to%20a%20layoff%2C%20resignation%2C%20job%20search%2C%20or%20shifting%20workplace%20expectations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EShare%20your%20story%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLSechTVqVWQve8iqYssNriCXdtwwdgGRixNNZpmslSKBQqIJ8g%2Fviewform%3Fusp%3Dheader%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efilling%20out%20this%20form%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20contacting%20this%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajzinkula%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejzinkula%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20via%20Signal%20at%20jzinkula.29.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2252a43e96-6b02-41bf-a42a-ca031ebe2118%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20was%20burned%20out%20at%20Microsoft%2C%20so%20I%20took%20a%20break%20before%20diving%20back%20into%20the%20job%20search%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20days%20after%20the%20layoff%2C%20I%20wasn't%20eager%20to%20jump%20back%20into%20the%20job%20market%20right%20away%2C%20so%20I%20took%20a%20year%20to%20reset%20and%20figure%20out%20what%20I%20really%20wanted%20next.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20factors%20led%20me%20to%20delay%20my%20job%20search.%20For%20one%2C%20I%20felt%20I%20needed%20to%20reset%20and%20give%20myself%20a%20mental%20break.%20During%20the%20period%20when%20my%20roles%20were%20changing%2C%20it%20felt%20like%20every%20time%20I%20would%20start%20to%20master%20a%20new%20position%2C%20I%20was%20bumped%20into%20a%20new%20one.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20it%2C%20I%20was%20really%20burned%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20also%20in%20a%20decent%20place%2C%20financially.%20I%20received%20a%20couple%20of%20extra%20months%20of%20paychecks%20before%20getting%20my%20severance%2C%20and%20was%20also%20able%20to%20extend%20my%20health%20insurance.%20I%20was%20also%20privileged%20to%20have%20enough%20savings%20to%20get%20by%20for%20a%20while%2C%20and%20my%20husband%20still%20had%20his%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20knew%20I'd%20eventually%20need%20to%20get%20back%20to%20work%2C%20though%2C%20and%20around%20July%202024%2C%20I%20started%20actively%20job%20searching.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229d0847c1-dbbc-49b1-a57a-8af57ef1beb3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECompanies'%20hiring%20plans%20seem%20to%20constantly%20be%20changing%2C%20which%20is%20frustrating%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20dove%20back%20in%2C%20I%20started%20reconnecting%20with%20people%20and%20browsing%20websites%20like%20Indeed%20and%20LinkedIn%20for%20roles%20similar%20to%20mine%20at%20Microsoft%2C%20including%20leadership%2C%20sales%2C%20and%20account%20executive%20roles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20gone%20to%20a%20couple%20of%20in-person%20job%20fairs%3B%20I%20think%20I'm%20better%20in%20person%20than%20I%20am%20on%20paper.%20I've%20also%20shared%20my%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20with%20my%20network%20before%20applying%20for%20roles%2C%20which%20has%20helped%20me%20land%20interviews%2C%20but%20they%20just%20haven't%20worked%20out%20in%20the%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20frustrating%20aspects%20of%20the%20job%20search%20process%20has%20been%20the%20seemingly%20constant%20evolution%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-market-2026-great-freeze-hiring-layoffs-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompanies'%20hiring%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Companies%20don't%20seem%20clear%20about%20whether%20roles%20will%20even%20exist%20for%20long%20after%20hiring%20people%20for%20them%2C%20and%20I've%20heard%20about%20people%20being%20laid%20off%2C%20finding%20new%20roles%20within%20the%20same%20company%2C%20and%20then%20being%20laid%20off%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fg5mgr%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Share%20of%20unemployed%20who%20are%20long-term%20unemployed%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22467%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227bceaf51-b606-4068-a7b4-1486770a2588%5C%22%3EI'm%20exploring%20a%20career%20pivot%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20realized%20that%20the%20part%20of%20my%20job%20I%20loved%20most%20was%20leading%20and%20coaching%20people.%20Compared%20to%20the%20bonuses%20and%20acknowledgments%20I%20received%20as%20a%20leader%2C%20none%20of%20that%20compared%20to%20the%20fulfillment%20of%20helping%20my%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20considering%20building%20my%20own%20business%20and%20began%20working%20toward%20life%20coaching%20certifications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20applied%20for%20some%20coaching%20roles%20and%20worked%20on%20my%20own%20coaching%20business%20by%20earning%20multiple%20certifications%20and%20launching%20my%20own%20website.%20I've%20recently%20begun%20working%20on%20partnering%20with%20my%20mother%2C%20who's%20a%20clinical%20psychologist%2C%20to%20offer%20both%20our%20services%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20believe%20pursuing%20an%20independent%20source%20of%20income%20is%20worthwhile%2C%20particularly%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-market-tough-for-every-generation-layoffs-great-flattening-careers-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etough%20job%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20seeming%20lack%20of%20job%20security%20these%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a90dce0c-616f-4472-b39a-5a46d5fc5fe7%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20believe%20that%20everything%20happens%20for%20a%20reason%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20job%20search%20has%20been%20hard%20for%20my%20husband%20and%20two%20kids%2C%20financially.%20We're%20in%20an%20OK%20spot%20thanks%20to%20my%20husband%20taking%20a%20lot%20of%20extra%20shifts%2C%20but%20it's%20hard%20not%20to%20contribute%20financially%2C%20the%20way%20I%20used%20to.%20We've%20also%20become%20more%20mindful%20of%20our%20spending%2C%20including%20budgeting%20for%20things%20we%20used%20to%20not%20even%20think%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMentally%2C%20it's%20been%20hard%20being%20in%20such%20a%20long%20career%20transition%2C%20but%20I%20know%20I'm%20not%20the%20only%20one.%20I%20regularly%20see%20posts%20on%20LinkedIn%20from%20former%20leaders%20who%20are%20still%20struggling%20to%20find%20work%2C%20as%20some%20companies%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiddle-manager-hiring-white-collar-recession-layoffs-jobs-efficiency-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecut%20leadership%20or%20manager%20roles%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20boost%20productivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20these%20challenges%2C%20I'm%20a%20firm%20believer%20that%20things%20happen%20for%20a%20reason%2C%20and%20I%20have%20no%20resentment%20toward%20Microsoft.%20If%20I%20had%20never%20been%20laid%20off%2C%20I%20think%20I'd%20stil